<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42066b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42066b">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42066b"> 66(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> orange, date, colocynth</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The state of a Muslim who readeth the Koran is like the <mark>orange</mark> fruit, whose smell and taste are pleasant; and that of a muslim who doth not read the Koran, is like a <mark>date</mark> which hath no smell, but a sweet taste; and the condition of any hypocrite who doth not read the Koran is like the <mark>colocynth</mark> which hath no smell, but a bitter taste <small> Stanley Lane-Poole, <a name="SLPS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SLPS"><cite title="source">The Speeches and Table-Talk of the Prophet Mohammad</cite></a> (1882) 154</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
